{
	"name": "Garlic, Pilgrim’s",
	"type": "object",
	"img": "icons/consumables/vegetable/garlic-lautrec-pink.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Garlic is a widely recognized plant, the pungent odor of its bulb making it easy to identify. It has tall green stalks, with pinkish-purple flower clusters. Common garlic is grown in gardens across the land, and the rarer pilgrim’s garlic can also be found in meadows and forests. Pilgrim’s garlic is usually mistaken for its common cousin, and while both function equally in various cuisines, pilgrim’s garlic is also a powerful antiseptic. Crushed cloves are effectively used to prevent infection in wounds.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect. </strong></em>If you have received a disease from a wound, applying a pilgrim’s garlic poultice to the wound enables you to repeat the saving throw you made against contracting the disease. Pilgrim’s garlic will only provide one additional save total for any given disease; additional doses have no effect. Any disease which can't normally be cured is also immune to garlic.</p>",
